```

In this version, we create an array fibArray of size n+1, and initialize it with the first two numbers in the sequence (0 and 1). We then use a loop that starts from the third number (i.e., 2) and iterates up to n, computing each number in the sequence as the sum of the two preceding ones, and storing the computed values in the array. Finally, we return the value of fibArray[n], which is the nth number in the sequence. Note that we use the same array to store the computed values as we use to return the nth number, so we avoid the overhead of computing and returning each number separately.

