1. Choose a microcontroller with an SPI interface and enough processing power to perform the image processing algorithms.
2. Select a high-resolution display that is compatible with the microcontroller and has an SPI interface.
3. Develop a code that initializes the SPI interface and the display, and sets up the microcontroller for image processing.
4. Implement the image processing algorithms, such as edge detection and motion tracking, using C code.
5. Use the SPI interface to transfer the processed image data to the display.
6. Continuously update the display with the processed image data.

Here is a simple example of how you can initialize the SPI interface in C code:

```c
#include <avr/io.h>

void init_SPI()
{
    // Set SPI mode to master, clock speed to f/4
    SPCR = (1<<SPE) | (1<<MSTR);
    SPSR = (1<<SPI2X);
    
    // Set data order to MSB first
    SPCR |= (1<<DORD);
    
    // Set clock polarity and phase to 0 and 1, respectively
    SPCR &= ~(1<<CPOL);
    SPCR |= (1<<CPHA);
    
    // Set chip select to output, and set it high
    DDRB |= (1<<PB2);
    PORTB |= (1<<PB2);
}
```

Once the SPI interface is initialized, you can use SPI transfer functions to send image data to the display. For example:

```c
void write_display(uint16_t data)
{
    // Set chip select low
    PORTB &= ~(1<<PB2);
    
    // Send high byte of data
    SPDR = (data >> 8) & 0xFF;
    while(!(SPSR & (1<<SPIF)));
    
    // Send low byte of data
    SPDR = data & 0xFF;
    while(!(SPSR & (1<<SPIF)));
    
    // Set chip select high
    PORTB |= (1<<PB2);
}
```

To implement image processing algorithms, you can use standard C libraries such as OpenCV or write your own algorithms. For example, here is a simple implementation of edge detection using the Sobel operator:

```c
void edge_detection(uint8_t* image, uint8_t* edges, uint16_t width, uint16_t height)
{
    int sobel_x[3][3] = {{-1, 0, 1}, {-2, 0, 2}, {-1, 0, 1}};
    int sobel_y[3][3] = {{-1, -2, -1}, {0, 0, 0}, {1, 2, 1}};
    
    for(int y = 1; y < height-1; y++)
    {
        for(int x = 1; x < width-1; x++)
        {
            int gx = 0, gy = 0;
            for(int j = 0; j < 3; j++)
            {
                for(int i = 0; i < 3; i++)
                {
                    gx += image[(y+j-1)*width + (x+i-1)] * sobel_x[j][i];
                    gy += image[(y+j-1)*width + (x+i-1)] * sobel_y[j][i];
                }
            }
            edges[y*width + x] = abs(gx) + abs(gy);
        }
    }
}
```

