You can implement image preview when using `react`, `MUI`, and `react-hook-form` to create a drag-and-drop component by following these steps:

1. Install dependencies: First, you need to install the necessary dependencies such as `react-dropzone`, `react-image-uploader`, and `react-hook-form`. You can install these dependencies using the following commands:

```
npm install @material-ui/core react-hook-form react-dropzone react-image-uploader
```

2. Create the `DropzoneInputControl` component: This component will manage the form control behavior. It will receive the `control` and `name` props from `react-hook-form`, and wrap the `DropzoneInput` component.

```javascript
import React from 'react';
import { useController } from 'react-hook-form';
import DropzoneInput from './DropzoneInput';

const DropzoneInputControl = ({ control, name }) => {
  const {
    field: { value, onChange, onBlur },
    fieldState: { error },
  } = useController({
    name,
    control,
    defaultValue: [],
  });

  return (
    <DropzoneInput
      value={value}
      onChange={onChange}
      onBlur={onBlur}
      error={!!error}
      helperText={error ? error.message : null}
    />
  );
};

export default DropzoneInputControl;
```

3. Create the `DropzoneInput` component: This component will wrap the `Dropzone` component from `MUI`. It will receive the `value`, `onChange`, `onBlur`, `error`, and `helperText` props from `DropzoneInputControl`. It will also use the `react-image-uploader` library to display image previews.

```javascript
import React, { useCallback } from 'react';
import { useDropzone } from 'react-dropzone';
import { makeStyles } from '@material-ui/core/styles';
import { Grid, Typography } from '@material-ui/core';
import ImageUploader from 'react-image-uploader';

const useStyles = makeStyles(() => ({
  dropzone: {
    display: 'flex',
    flexDirection: 'column',
    alignItems: 'center',
    padding: '20px',
    borderWidth: '2px',
    borderRadius: '2px',
    borderColor: '#eeeeee',
    borderStyle: 'dashed',
    backgroundColor: '#fafafa',
    color: '#bdbdbd',
    outline: 'none',
    transition: 'border .24s ease-in-out',
    minHeight: '200px',
  },
  error: {
    borderColor: 'red',
    color: 'red',
  },
}));

const DropzoneInput = ({ value, onChange, onBlur, error, helperText }) => {
  const classes = useStyles();

  const handleDrop = useCallback(
    (acceptedFiles) => {
      const files = acceptedFiles.map((file) =>
        Object.assign(file, {
          preview: URL.createObjectURL(file),
        })
      );
      onChange(files);
    },
    [onChange]
  );

  const { getRootProps, getInputProps, isDragActive } = useDropzone({
    accept: 'image/*',
    maxSize: 5242880, //5MB
    multiple: true,
    onDrop: handleDrop,
  });

  return (
    <div
      {...getRootProps()}
      className={`${classes.dropzone} ${error ? classes.error : ''}`}
    >
      <input {...getInputProps()} onBlur={onBlur} />
      {value.length > 0 ? (
        <Grid container spacing={1}>
          {value.map((file) => (
            <Grid item xs={4} key={file.name}>
              <ImageUploader
                withIcon={false}
                withPreview={true}
                singleImage={true}
                withLabel={false}
                buttonText="Upload"
                label={file.name}
                imgExtension={['.jpg', '.jpeg', '.png', '.gif']}
                maxFileSize={5242880}
                fileSizeError="File size too large (5MB max)"
                fileTypeError="Unsupported file type"
                errorClass={classes.error}
                file={file}
                onChange={onChange}
              />
            </Grid>
          ))}
        </Grid>
      ) : isDragActive ? (
        <Typography variant="body1">
          Drop the files here ...
        </Typography>
      ) : (
        <Typography variant="body1">
          Drag 'n' drop some files here, or click to select files
        </Typography>
      )}
      {helperText && (
        <Typography variant="body2" className={classes.error}>
          {helperText}
        </Typography>
      )}
    </div>
  );
};

export default DropzoneInput;
```

4. Create the parent component: This component will render the `DropzoneInputControl` component, and will also implement the `uploadFile` function provided through a prop. The `handleSubmit` function will be called when the form is submitted. It will call the `uploadFile` function, and pass it the uploaded files.

```javascript
import React from 'react';
import { useForm } from 'react-hook-form';
import { Grid, Button } from '@material-ui/core';
import DropzoneInputControl from './DropzoneInputControl';

const ParentComponent = ({ uploadFile }) => {
  const {
    control,
    handleSubmit,
    formState: { isSubmitting },
  } = useForm();

  const onSubmit = async (data) => {
    try {
      await uploadFile(data.files);
    } catch (error) {
      console.log(error);
    }
  };

  return (
    <form onSubmit={handleSubmit(onSubmit)}>
      <Grid container spacing={2}>
        <Grid item xs={12}>
          <DropzoneInputControl control={control} name="files" />
        </Grid>
        <Grid item xs={12}>
          <Button
            type="submit"
            variant="contained"
            color="primary"
            disabled={isSubmitting}
          >
            Submit
          </Button>
        </Grid>
      </Grid>
    </form>
  );
};

export default ParentComponent;
```

You can now use the `ParentComponent` in your app, and pass it the `uploadFile` function as a prop. The `uploadFile` function should handle the uploading of files to your server.

