Fn = (phi^n - psi^n) / sqrt5

where phi is the golden ratio, psi is its conjugate, and sqrt5 is the square root of 5. To modify the given C++ code to print the first 20 Fibonacci numbers, we need to adjust the value of n to 20 and calculate the nth term of the sequence using the formula above. Here are the steps to achieve this:

